  <text>
      <body>
         <p>Dear Sir,</p>
         <p><persName ref="prsn:Carl03">Alfred</persName> and I together have started a new publication entitled "The Church". The speculation is his: the labour of editing mine.</p>
         <p>I write to let you know it and that you may make it known.</p>
         <p>l left <placeName ref="tgn:7010477">Manchester</placeName>  on Easter Sunday, had a set to with <persName ref="prsn:Finc01">Finch[?]</persName> the Socialist in <placeName ref="tgn:7010597">Liverpool</placeName> that evening - came to <placeName ref="tgn:7010534">Bolton</placeName> the next day and had a set to with <persName ref="prsn:Acla01">Mr Acland</persName> in the <placeName ref="plc:Bolt01">Bolton Theatre</placeName> on tuesday evening. Came on to <placeName ref="tgn:7010955">Birmingham</placeName> on the wednesday, thence to <placeName ref="tgn:7011192">Cheltenham</placeName> to visit my new and great and good friends, with whom I spent a most happy week.—</p>
         <p>Reached <placeName ref="plc:Enfi01">Enfield High Way</placeName> on sunday last to see a No or two of The Church. hence I go to <placeName ref="tgn:7010831"><choice><sic>Wisbeach</sic><corr>Wisbech</corr></choice></placeName>, <placeName ref="tgn:7010791"><choice><abbr>Lynn</abbr><expan>King's Lynn</expan></choice></placeName>, <placeName ref="tgn:7012005">Norwich</placeName>, <placeName ref="tgn:7010782"><choice><abbr>Yarmouth</abbr><expan>Great Yarmouth</expan></choice></placeName> and <placeName ref="tgn:1028689">Bungay</placeName>, perhaps <placeName ref="tgn:7010914">Bury St <choice><sic>Edmonds</sic><corr>Edmunds</corr></choice></placeName>. Shall return to <placeName ref="tgn:7011781">London</placeName> [[2]] toward the end of June – go hence to <placeName ref="tgn:7011192">Cheltenham</placeName> <placeName ref="tgn:7015155">Worcester</placeName>, <placeName ref="tgn:7010955">Birmingham</placeName>, the <placeName ref="tgn:7459382">Potteries</placeName> and back to <placeName ref="tgn:7010477">Manchester</placeName>: thence to <placeName ref="tgn:7010692">Sheffield</placeName> some day. <persName ref="prsn:Shar01">Mrs C.</persName> will now travel and lecture under my travelling name of Mrs Clay.— While I am absent from <placeName ref="tgn:7010477">Manchester</placeName> my room is occupied by the Socialists among whom I hear there is a split.</p>
         <p>I have no particular news to tell you, save that my prospects improve, which I know will be pleasant news to you.</p> 
         <p>I have left <persName ref="prsn:Carl02">Tom</persName> in <placeName ref="tgn:7010477">Manchester</placeName>, not knowing what to do with him, and am trying to get him a shop there. If he does well, he will agreeably disappoint me.</p>
         <p>I will look about for your Diegesis next week.</p>
         <p>love to your family. respectfully</p>
         <p>R. Carlile</p>
         
      </body>
